arts.ttl: Erling Haaland scores five as Norway put 11 past Moldova
arts.sum: The Manchester City forward enjoyed a goal glut, while Arsenal’s Martin Odegaard was also on the scoresheet

arts.ttl: Erling Haaland scores 5 with stitches as Norway routs Moldova 11-1 in World Cup qualifying
arts.sum: Bearing stitches on his face from a bizarre accident with a bus door, Erling Haaland made his mark for the Norwegian national team by scoring five goals in an 11-1 win over Moldova in World Cup qualifying Tuesday. It was the biggest win of this World Cup qualifying cycle in Europe, surpassing an 8-0 victory for the Netherlands over Malta in June, and came close to the all-time European qualification record, a 12-0 win by West Germany against Cyprus in 1969.

arts.ttl: Norway 11-1 Moldova: Erling Haaland scores five as minnows subject to devastating rout
arts.sum: Thelo Aasgaard scored four in the second half to continue the demolition job

arts.ttl: Erling Haaland scored five goals for Norway in their 11-1 win over Moldova.
arts.sum: Erling Haaland scored five goals and added two assists in Norway’s emphatic win over Moldova. To emphasise this point, Erling Haaland scored five goals for Norway in their 11-1 win over Moldova.

arts.ttl: Haaland requires stitches in face after bizarre incident on Norway duty but OK to play Moldova
arts.sum: Erling Haaland is “doing fine” after requiring stitches for a cut to his face sustained in a bizarre incident on international duty with Norway, team captain Martin Ødegaard said Monday. The Manchester City star posted a photo on Snapchat on Sunday showing the facial injury he reportedly suffered when being hit by a luggage door as he got off Norway’s team bus before walking into a hotel.
